{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2a3b1283-e31e-4f4a-a7ed-97a204dc3e21","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if the exception is thrown *anywhere* in the test — even in the arrange step — masking bugs.\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` scopes the check to the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, properties, inner exception).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad06a30b-5f70-4f22-a869-64c97a795c1d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":238,"requestId":"67CF:CA1D0:2C556A8:30F07C5:69FD3E22"},"id":"9315ceaf-b949-4a0d-ac41-8ffcc25f9718","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:36:43.281Z","parentId":"24daa72b-f63f-4d03-b2a0-3968b13a8944"}
